Optogenetics can also be used for some form of neuronal circuit mapping or connectome mapping, see: [Rapid learning of neural circuitry from holographic ensemble stimulation enabled by model-based compressed sensing](https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2022.09.14.507926v3.abstract) or this [compressive sensing ref](https://www.cell.com/patterns/fulltext/S2666-3899(23)00224-6).


Besides using optogenetics to stimulate cells or neurons, you can also use GFP and other techniques to get data out of cells, such as genetically encoded voltage indicators (which are an alternative to various fluorescent dyes). See [Voltron2: Sensitivity optimization of a rhodopsin-based genetically encoded fluorescent voltage indicator](https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0896627323002052).


